aho state historical society"], "date": "1914-02-05", "dates": ["1914-02-05"], "description": ["THE NEZPERCE HERALD THURSDAY FEB 5 1914 w p rur m r w xueau Sdlton and Own How Hug Cholera is Being Combatted Washington D C Jan 31 The Department of agriculture during the past year has been conducting a campaign in Indiana Missouri Iowa and Nebraska to control the contag ious disease of bogs known as hog cholera by means of antihog chol era serum and farm quarantines In one county Pettis county Missouri where there was a loss of 18 per cent In 1911 and 356 per cent in 1913 of all hogs raised there was only a loss of 147 per cent up to November 1913 This decrease was due to the use of serum which although not used there by the Departments agents until August 1913 material ly reduced the loss About 60000 hogs were raised during the past year and of the 10000 that died of the hog cholera only about 1000 were lost after the active use of ser um and quarantine measures were inaugurated In every country where these meas ures were employed even though be gun after the disease had continued its ravages for some time there was le lost from hog"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-07-06T12:36:51.300Z", "group": ["ndnp/idhi", "idaho-state-historical-society-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn89055082/1914-02-05/ed-1/?sp=4", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:idhi:batch_idhi_jerusalem_ver01:data:sn89055082:00414211148:1914020501:0046/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=403&w=270", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:idhi:batch_idhi_jerusalem_ver01:data:sn89055082:00414211148:1914020501:0046/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=807&w=541", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/idhi/batch_idhi_jerusalem_ver01/data/sn89055082/00414211148/1914020501/0046.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["nez perce", "idaho", "nezperc